<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Woman stabbed to death at rest stop on I-40  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MORRILTON, Ark. (AP) - A 25-year-old woman from New Jersey was
found stabbed to death at an Interstate 40 rest stop near
Morrilton, Ark., Conway County Sheriff Mark Flowers said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The woman, whose name was withheld by Flowers, was stabbed and
her nude body was left on the bank of a nearby pond, the sheriff
said.
</P>
<P>
   The woman was driving with her two dogs from her home state to
California. A trucker spotted the dogs running loose late Saturday
afternoon and called a phone number on one of the dogs' tags. The
trucker reached the woman's mother who told the trucker something
must be wrong, Flowers said.
</P>
<P>
   The trucker called authorities, who found the body while
searching the area.
</P>
<P>
   Flowers said he was awaiting autopsy results to learn the cause
of death.
</P>
</TEXT>
