<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 02:31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hand Grenade Explodes in Jakarta  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) -- A hand grenade exploded in the parking
lot of the Malaysian embassy in Jakarta, employees said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   There were no injuries from Sunday night's blast and only slight
damage was caused to the pavement, employees said. Police found the
release lever from a hand grenade near a small crater.
</P>
<P>
   The blast was the third explosion in Indonesia during the
weekend.
</P>
<P>
   On Sunday, two small bombs exploded in the third-largest city of
Medan, police said. Nobody claimed responsibility for the blasts,
which also caused no injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Indonesia has been hit by a new wave of unexplained bomb attacks
recently.
</P>
<P>
   The worst happened Aug. 1 outside the residence of Philippine
Ambassador Leonides Caday. It killed two people and injured dozens,
including Caday.
</P>
</TEXT>
