<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 10:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 49; Nasdaq Adds 7  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks advanced in early trading Monday, a
possible indication that investors are more confident about the
future direction of stock prices after several indecisive sessions.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was up 49.48 at 11,242.11.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 index was up 4.24 at 1,510.70, and the Nasdaq composite index
was up 7.07 at 4,049.75.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks fluctuated last week, while mostly moving higher, as
investors digested the new landscape now that interest rate hikes
seem to no longer be a factor in trading.
</P>
<P>
   But the move upward has lacked conviction, in part, because
energy prices remain high and labor markets tight -- both factors
that could contribute to a rise in inflation. In addition, several
sectors have warned that profits may be down in the second half of
2000.
</P>
<P>
   These dynamics could pose obstacles as the markets try to
reclaim their highs of early spring.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues narrowly outnumbered decliners on the New York
Stock Exchange, where volume came to 83.57 million shares, down
from Friday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index up 1.47 at 526.58.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average rose 1.60 percent. In
afternoon trading, Germany's DAX index was up 0.28 percent,
Britain's FT-SE 100 was up 0.10 percent, and France's CAC-40 was
down 0.08 percent.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
