<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Adds 85; Nasdaq Gains 43  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks surged higher Monday, a possible
indication that investors are more confident about the future
direction of stock prices after several indecisive sessions.
</P>
<P>
   In midmorning trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 84.62 at 11,277.25.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 index was up 12.77 at 1,519.23, and the Nasdaq composite index
was up 43.32 at 4,086.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks fluctuated last week, while mostly moving higher, as
investors digested the new landscape now that interest rate hikes
seem to no longer be a factor in trading.
</P>
<P>
   ''Investors have been extremely lackadaisical in the past few
sessions,'' said Don Hays, president of Hays Advisory Group in
Nashville, Tenn. ''People seem comfortable that there won't be any
more interest rate hikes.''
</P>
<P>
   But the move upward has lacked conviction, in part, because
energy prices remain high and labor markets tight -- both factors
that could contribute to a rise in inflation. In addition, several
sectors have warned that profits may be down in the second half of
2000.
</P>
<P>
   These dynamics could pose obstacles as the markets try to
reclaim their highs of early spring.
</P>
<P>
   Hays noted that trading volume on Friday was at its lowest level
of the year and remained low Monday. Moreover, he noted that stocks
were being propelled on Monday on the strength of a handful of
stocks in a small number of sectors, something known as a lack of
breadth in the market.
</P>
<P>
   The blue-chip index was led by widely held stocks such as IBM,
up $2.625 to $131.625, and J.P. Morgan, up $146.75.
</P>
<P>
   And Internet stocks, out of favor since the spring, have moved
back into the spotlight, helping to fuel the Nasdaq. Online
retailer Amazon.com rose 87.50 cents to $40.813.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 7-to-5 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 211.82 million
shares, down from Friday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was up 3.34 at 528.45.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
