<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 20:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reds' Williamson on Disabled List  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Cincinnati pitcher Scott Williamson, bothered by
a lower back strain, was placed on the 15-day disabled list Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Reds recalled John Riedling from Triple-A Louisville. The
right-hander was en route to Atlanta and expected to arrive during
Monday night's game against the Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Williamson (5-7, 3.16 ERA) has developed into Cincinnati's best
starter since he was moved from the bullpen to the rotation on July
9. He has allowed more than three earned runs only once in nine
starts and pitched at least six innings six times.
</P>
<P>
   In his last start, Williamson limited Philadelphia to one run
and four hits over seven innings Wednesday, but did not figure in
the decision. The Reds lost 4-3.
</P>
<P>
   Williamson was placed on the DL, retroactive to Thursday, after
returning to Cincinnati for an examination. Ron Villone (8-7)
stepped in to make his first start since July 22.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
