<HEADLINE> Ramirez Dislocates Shoulder  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Pittsburgh Pirates third baseman Aramis
Ramirez partially dislocated his left shoulder diving for Ellis
Burks' double down the line in the first inning Monday against San
Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez left the game and was taken to a hospital for X-rays.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez was clutching his left hand as he left the field, but an
examination in the clubhouse revealed the shoulder injury.
</P>
