</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- A federal judge has approved a proposed $3.75 billion
national settlement of claims involving the diet drug combination fen-phen,
which has been linked to potentially fatal heart valve damage. Under the
settlement, fen-phen users would get up to $1.5 million, though most would get
far less, depending on their circumstances.
</P>
