nationwide survey said they were made to perform humiliating or illegal acts to
join athletic teams, the band, even church groups, university researchers said
today. The researchers at Alfred University in Alfred, N.Y. -- known for studies
of college hazing -- said the report on high schools shows the vulnerability of
younger people.
