<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 21:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Packers Coach: Favre Will Play Jets  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Packers quarterback Brett Favre, who
missed Green Bay's last three preseason games with tendinitis in
his right elbow, should start the season opener against the Jets.
</P>
<P>
   ''I have high expectations that he will play in the game,''
Packers coach Mike Sherman said Monday. ''If he doesn't, it will be
a shock to me. There are no indicators at this time that says he
won't be able to play. Nothing is showing us he won't be Brett
Favre again when we play on Sunday.''
</P>
<P>
   The decision to rest Favre for the three preseason contests
ended his string of starts that stretched back 173 preseason,
regular season and postseason games. He took over as starter three
games into the 1992 season and has held the job ever since.
</P>
<P>
   If he opens against the Jets at Lambeau Field it will be his
126th consecutive regular-season start.
</P>
<P>
   Favre has tested the arm in recent days, throwing 50 passes
Sunday and throwing again Monday. He was not expected to throw in
workouts Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Offensive coordinator Tom Rossley expects Favre to throw close
to full speed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Sherman said Favre likely will experience some soreness after
using the arm, but that is expected.
</P>
<P>
   Both Favre and backup Matt Hasselbeck will take practice snaps
with the first-team offense.
</P>
<P>
   ''There's absolutely no concern about Favre,'' Packers general
manager Ron Wolf said. ''I have to believe what everybody says is
true is true -- that he's going to go play.''
</P>
<P>
   Running back Dorsey Levens appears to have no chance of playing
against New York. Levens missed the last two games with knee
tendinitis.
</P>
<P>
   ''It would be foolish to try to push him, coming off a surgery
(Aug. 15) to come back this quickly,'' Sherman said.
</P>
<P>
   Levens' backup, Ahman Green, could play Sunday. Green also
missed the last two preseason games with a sprained knee.
</P>
<P>
   ''Ahman has been able to push extremely hard straight ahead,''
Sherman said. ''It's the lateral movement that will be the
question.''
</P>
<P>
   If Green cannot play, the Packers expect to start either rookie
Herbert Goodman or Basil Mitchell.
</P>
<P>
   Sherman said defensive tackle Santana Dotson (knee) will
practice Wednesday and play Sunday. Meanwhile, linebacker Bernardo
Harris (bruised knee) has a 50-50 chance of playing against the
Jets. If Harris doesn't start, Mike Morton will replace him.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the trade the Packers made with Oakland on Sunday for
defensive tackle Chuck Osborne was voided Monday when Osborne
failed his physical. The Packers had traded a fifth-round pick in
2002 for Osborne.
</P>
<P>
   In other moves Monday, the Packers claimed tight end Chris
Eitzmann on waivers from New England and linebacker Chris Gizzi on
waivers from Denver.
</P>
<P>
   The Packers cut third-year linebacker Jude Waddy.
</P>
<P>
   Green Bay signed guard Craig Heimburger, defensive end Kabeer
Gbaja-Biamila and linebacker Eugene McCaslin to the practice squad.
The three had been waived Sunday and became free agents after
clearing 24-hour waivers.
</P>
<P>
   The Packers have two more openings on the practice squad.
</P>
</TEXT>
