<HEADLINE> Five men indicted on charges they ran sports betting operations  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - Five men were indicted Monday on charges
they ran sports betting operations in three counties, according to
the state attorney general's office.
</P>
<P>
   Tung T. Nguyen, 28, and Truyen T. Vo, 35, both of East Hanover;
Tung V. Nguyen, 32, of Plainfield; and Tu Van Doan, 32, and Tuan M.
Nguyen, 34, both of South Plainfield, were indicted, the attorney
general's office said.
</P>
<P>
   Tung T. Nguyen and Vo were indicted on charges they promoted
gambling and possessed gambling records on Nov. 17, 1998 in East
Hanover, Morris County and Bernardsville, Somerset County,
authorities said. Vo was also indicted on charges of filing
fraudulent state income tax returns in the years 1995-98 and
failing to pay state income tax for those years, according to
authorities.
</P>
<P>
   Van Doan, Tuan Nguyen and Tung V. Nguyen were indicted on
similar gambling charges related to events on Dec. 29, 1998 in
South Plainfield, Middlesex County, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   All of the charges carry up to five years in jail and fines of
$15,00 for each count.
</P>
<P>
   An attorney general's office spokeswoman said the indictments
did not specify what type of sporting events they defendants
accepted bets on.
</P>
</TEXT>
