<HEADLINE> Millwood Breaks Nose in Practice  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Braves pitcher Kevin Millwood wound up with a
broken nose and deviated septum while working on his bunting in the
indoor batting cage at Turner Field before Monday night's game
against the Cincinnati Reds.
</P>
<P>
   Millwood bunted the ball and it bounced back up and hit him in
the nose, said team spokesman Jim Schultz. He is still expected to
make his scheduled start Thursday against the Reds in the finale of
a four-game series.
</P>
