<HEADLINE> Turner Awarded Year of Eligibility  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Southern California forward Jarvis Turner,
whose college career appeared over, has been awarded a fifth year
of eligibility by the NCAA for medical hardship.
</P>
<P>
   ''It is great to have a veteran guy like Jarvis Turner back on
the team because he knows what it takes to win,'' USC coach Henry
Bibby said Monday. ''He's had a tough career at USC because of
injuries and hopefully he can make the most of this opportunity.
It's good to have another player on the bench who we know we can
count on.''
</P>
<P>
   Turner, a 6-foot-8, 240-pounder, played in only seven of USC's
30 games last season because of various foot injuries, averaging
1.7 points and 1.6 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Turner has started 23 times in 74 career games and averaged 6.5
points and 3.7 rebounds. As a sophomore in the 1997-98 season, he
averaged 10.6 points and 5.3 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   USC returns all five starters from last year's team, which
finished 16-14.
</P>
