<HEADLINE> Single pilot plane lands safely on Thruway  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SCHENECTADY, N.Y. (AP) - Engine problems forced the pilot of a
single-engine plane to use a Thruway ramp as a last-ditch landing
strip Monday.
</P>
<P>
   State police say Mark Wielt of Altamont landed his Piper Cub
safely on the ramp leading to the toll plaza at Exit 25A on
Interstate-90, which heads into Duanesburg, at about 6:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   There were no injuries, no damage to Thruway property or the
plane, and no road closures.
</P>
<P>
   It was the second highway landing in New York state this year.
</P>
<P>
   In March, a single-engine plane carrying three passengers made
an emergency landing in Canajoharie. There were no injuries in that
landing either.
</P>
