<HEADLINE> Concertgoer attacked with hatchet  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) - A Pennsylvania man said Monday that he has
no idea why somebody attacked him with a hatchet when he was
attending a rock concert.
</P>
<P>
   ''I got knocked down,'' said Chris Schneck, 21, a waiter from
Newtown, Bucks County. ''I really didn't know what happened, and
then when I woke up my hand was pretty much cut.''
</P>
<P>
   Schneck had just left the Creed concert at the E-Center on
Saturday night when someone attacked his friend with a piece of
lumber in the parking lot. Schneck said he was hit from behind as
he went to help.
</P>
<P>
   His father, Tom Schneck, said doctors described his nearly
severed hand as an injury you might see on a battlefield.
</P>
<P>
   The younger Schneck will undergo more surgery; doctors said
there is a good chance that he will not lose his right hand.
</P>
<P>
   The Schneck family is considering a lawsuit to bring about
tighter security.
</P>
