<HEADLINE> Emergency Landing for Northwest Jet  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- The crew of a Northwest Airlines jetliner carrying
380 people made an emergency landing at Tokyo's airport late Monday
after reporting engine trouble over the Pacific Ocean, airport
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The pilot of the Boeing 747 switched off the troubled No. 1
engine and landed safely at Narita airport, outside Tokyo, the
airport said.
</P>
<P>
   The jet has two engines on each wing, and the malfunctioning
engine was at the far end of the left wing.
</P>
<P>
   None of the 380 passengers or crew aboard Flight NW26 was
injured, Kyodo News agency said.
</P>
<P>
   The plane was en route from Osaka to Los Angeles, Kyodo said.
</P>
</TEXT>
